FBIS4-23132 "drafr104_d_94002" June Reports FBIS-AFR-94-104 Daily Report 29 May 1994 SOUTHERN AFRICA Angola Government Proposes To Give UNITA 4 Ministries Government Proposes To Give UNITA 4 Ministries MB2905182894 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 1730 GMT 29 May 94 MB2905182894 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network Portuguese BFN [Text] The Angolan Government has presented to the mediators of the peace talks in Lusaka a proposal for the participation of the National Union for the Total Independence of Angola [UNITA] in the government with four ministries. These are the ministries of health, tourism, geology and mines, and commerce. The Angolan Government also accorded UNITA seven deputy ministries -- public works, defense, agriculture, finance, social administration [title as heard], social communication, and interior. Savimbi's organization also received six embassies and 140 local administration posts. This was revealed by the Portuguese News Agency LUSA.
